---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Delete Account — Recursio"
  description="How to request deletion of your Recursio account and learning data."
  canonicalSlug="delete-account"
>
  <article class="legal-section">
    <h1>Delete Your Recursio Account</h1>
    <p>
      Users can request deletion of their Recursio account and account-linked learning data.
    </p>

    <h2>What May Be Deleted</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Account profile information</li>
      <li>Saved vocabulary</li>
      <li>Vocabulary spaces</li>
      <li>Practice history</li>
      <li>Grammar progress</li>
      <li>Coach history</li>
      <li>AI Writing attempts</li>
      <li>App-linked learning progress</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What May Be Retained</h2>
    <p>
      Some limited records may be retained if required for legal, security, fraud prevention,
      accounting, or app store subscription compliance reasons.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Request Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Send an email to
      <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a> with the subject:
      <strong>"Delete my Recursio account"</strong>
    </p>
    <p>Please include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The email address used for Apple or Google sign-in, if available</li>
      <li>The platform used: iOS or Android</li>
      <li>A short confirmation that you want your Recursio account deleted</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Processing Time</h2>
    <p>
      Deletion requests are usually processed within 30 days after verification.
    </p>

    <h2>Subscription Note</h2>
    <p>
      Deleting your account does not automatically cancel an App Store or Google Play
      subscription. You must cancel your subscription separately through your Apple or Google
      subscription settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
